### CSS Filters

**Filters** apply graphical effects like blur and color shifts to elements.

---

### Filter Functions

| Function | Example | Effect |
|----------|---------|--------|
| `blur()` | `blur(5px)` | Gaussian blur |
| `brightness()` | `brightness(1.5)` | Adjust brightness (0-1 = dark, 1+ = bright) |
| `contrast()` | `contrast(2)` | Adjust contrast |
| `drop-shadow()` | `drop-shadow(2px 2px 5px black)` | Shadow following element shape |
| `grayscale()` | `grayscale(100%)` | Convert to grayscale |
| `hue-rotate()` | `hue-rotate(90deg)` | Shift colors |
| `invert()` | `invert(100%)` | Invert colors |
| `opacity()` | `opacity(50%)` | Transparency |
| `saturate()` | `saturate(2)` | Increase saturation |
| `sepia()` | `sepia(100%)` | Sepia tone |
| `url()` | `url("filter.svg#filter")` | SVG filter reference |

---

### Blur

```css
.element {
  filter: blur(4px);
  filter: blur(0);   /* Sharp */
}
```

---

### Brightness & Contrast

```css
/* Darken image */
img.dark {
  filter: brightness(0.7);
}

/* Brighten */
img.light {
  filter: brightness(1.3);
}

/* High contrast */
img.high-contrast {
  filter: contrast(1.5);
}

/* Both */
img.filtered {
  filter: brightness(1.1) contrast(1.2);
}
```

---

### Grayscale & Sepia

```css
/* Black and white */
img.bw {
  filter: grayscale(100%);
}

/* Vintage */
img.vintage {
  filter: sepia(60%);
}

/* Hover to colorize */
img.desaturate {
  filter: grayscale(100%);
  transition: filter 0.3s;
}

img.desaturate:hover {
  filter: grayscale(0);
}
```

---

### Drop Shadow (vs Box Shadow)

```css
/* Box shadow - follows box shape */
box-shadow: 5px 5px 10px black;

/* Drop shadow - follows element outline (alpha-aware) */
filter: drop-shadow(5px 5px 10px black);
```

`drop-shadow()` respects `border-radius`, clipped content, and text outlines.

---

### Hue Rotate

```css
.filtered {
  filter: hue-rotate(180deg);  /* Shift all colors by 180 degrees */
}
```

---

### Multiple Filters

```css
.element {
  filter: brightness(1.2) contrast(1.3) saturate(1.5);
}
```

---

### Backdrop Filter

```css
.element {
  backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
  /* Blurs content BEHIND the element */
  /* Creates glass-morphism effect */
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Use `filter` for image effects and hover states. Use `backdrop-filter` for glass-morphism UI effects.
